4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PERMITTING THE COMMERCIAL BUYING, SELLING, TRADING,
5 AND DEALING OF SKINS AND PELTS OF BADGERS, RACOONS, RED FOXES, AND WOLVES BY FUR
6 DEALERS; REVISING THE DEFINITION OF "FUR DEALER"; REVISING PERSONS REQUIRED TO HAVE A
7 FUR DEALER'S LICENSE; AMENDING SECTIONS 87-4-301, 87-4-303, AND 87-6-101, MCA; AND
8 PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 87-4-301, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "87-4-301. Fur dealers defined. (1) A person or persons, firm, company, or corporation engaging in,
14 carrying on, or conducting wholly or in part the business of buying or selling, trading, or dealing within the state
15 of Montana in the skins or pelts of badgers, racoons, red foxes, wolves, or any animal or animals designated by
16 the laws of Montana as fur-bearing or predatory animals is considered a fur dealer within the meaning of this
17 part.
18 (2) If the fur dealer resides in or if the fur dealer's principal place of business is within the state of
19 Montana, the fur dealer is considered a resident fur dealer. All other fur dealers are considered nonresident fur
20 dealers."
21
22 Section 2. Section 87-4-303, MCA, is amended to read:
23 "87-4-303. Persons required to have fur dealer's license. A fur dealer shall, before buying, selling,
24 or in any manner dealing in the skins or pelts of badgers, racoons, red foxes, wolves, any fur-bearing animals,
25 or predatory animal animals within this state, secure a fur dealer's license from the director. A license is not
26 required for a hunter or trapper selling skins or pelts that the hunter or trapper has lawfully taken or for a person
27 who is not a fur dealer who purchases skins or pelts exclusively for the person's own use and not for sale."
